<refentryinfo><date>4.0</date></refentryinfo>
<refmeta>
<refentrytitle>Tk_DrawFocusHighlight</refentrytitle>
<manvolnum>3</manvolnum>
<refmiscinfo class='date'>4.0</refmiscinfo>
<refmiscinfo class='source'>Tk</refmiscinfo>
<refmiscinfo class='manual'>Tk Library Procedures</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>
<refnamediv>
<refname>Tk_DrawFocusHighlight</refname>
<refpurpose>draw the traversal highlight ring for a widget</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv xml:id='synopsis'>
<funcsynopsis>
<funcsynopsisinfo>
#include &lt;tk.h&gt;

</funcsynopsisinfo>
<funcprototype>
<funcdef><function>Tk_DrawFocusHighlight</function></funcdef>
<paramdef><parameter>tkwin</parameter></paramdef>
<paramdef><parameter>gc</parameter></paramdef>
<paramdef><parameter>width</parameter></paramdef>
<paramdef><parameter>drawable</parameter></paramdef>
</funcprototype>
</funcsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 xml:id='arguments'><title>ARGUMENTS</title>
<!-- .AS Tcl_Interp *joinPtr -->
<informaltable>
<tgroup cols='3'>
<tbody>

<row><entry>"Tk_Window"</entry><entry>"tkwin"</entry><entry>"in"</entry>
<entry>
<para>Window for which the highlight is being drawn.  Used to retrieve
the window's dimensions, among other things.</para>
</entry>
</row>
<row><entry>GC</entry><entry>gc</entry><entry>in</entry>
<entry>
<para>Graphics context to use for drawing the highlight.</para>
</entry>
</row>
<row><entry>int</entry><entry>width</entry><entry>in</entry>
<entry>
<para>Width of the highlight ring, in pixels.</para>
</entry>
</row>
<row><entry>Drawable</entry><entry>drawable</entry><entry>in</entry>
<entry>
<para>Drawable in which to draw the highlight;  usually an offscreen
pixmap for double buffering.</para>
<!-- .BE -->
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</informaltable>

</refsect1>

<refsect1 xml:id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para><function>Tk_DrawFocusHighlight</function> is a utility procedure that draws the
traversal highlight ring for a widget.
It is typically invoked by widgets during redisplay.</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1 xml:id='keywords'><title>KEYWORDS</title>
<para>focus, traversal highlight</para>
</refsect1>
